WEBVTT

00:00.867 --> 00:02.667
This is Nero.
Want to give me a kiss.

00:02.669 --> 00:06.939
Nero, bad apple,
rotten tree.

00:06.941 --> 00:08.673
Peter:
Something is up.

00:08.675 --> 00:11.876
You run with those dogs again,
they'll bury you 10 feet deep.

00:11.878 --> 00:14.879
I mean, Hodel might be
a lot of things...

00:14.881 --> 00:18.016
but he sure as hell
isn't the bogeyman.

00:18.018 --> 00:20.418
Hello. I'm Fauna.

00:20.420 --> 00:21.686
I'm George's
granddaughter.

00:21.688 --> 00:23.822
Come to find
my real mother, Tamar.

00:23.824 --> 00:25.157
You're not black.

00:25.159 --> 00:26.358
You're a lair.

00:26.360 --> 00:28.493
Jay:
Tamar got sent to a convent.

00:28.495 --> 00:32.965
They hide you till the baby's
born, and then -- whoosh! --

00:32.967 --> 00:35.367
you never see her again.

00:35.369 --> 00:36.969
Do you have a favorite?

00:36.971 --> 00:40.406
♪♪

00:45.245 --> 00:48.313
♪♪

00:54.188 --> 00:56.922
♪♪

00:59.326 --> 01:03.928
[ Animal lowing ]

01:03.930 --> 01:06.465
♪♪

01:06.467 --> 01:09.133
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:09.135 --> 01:11.570
♪♪

01:14.675 --> 01:17.009
♪♪

01:20.014 --> 01:24.016
Now you're anonymous.
I don't feel anonymous.

01:24.018 --> 01:28.020
♪♪

01:28.022 --> 01:31.156
Good evening, gentlemen.

01:31.158 --> 01:34.159
There you are.

01:34.161 --> 01:36.628
Are you ready
for tonight?

01:36.630 --> 01:40.833
[ Indistinct conversations
continue ]

01:40.835 --> 01:42.967
Do you like
what's on the menu?

01:42.969 --> 01:44.369
Hodel: Hello, my angel.

01:44.371 --> 01:49.908
♪♪

01:49.910 --> 01:51.109
Tamar.

01:51.111 --> 01:55.247
♪♪

01:55.249 --> 01:58.783
Tamar,
are you dreaming again?

01:58.785 --> 02:01.720
♪♪

02:05.259 --> 02:08.060
♪♪

02:11.998 --> 02:14.900
♪♪

02:18.472 --> 02:22.408
Take this kiss upon the brow...

02:24.478 --> 02:26.879
...and in parting
from you now...

02:29.616 --> 02:32.718
...thus much let me avow...

02:34.555 --> 02:35.888
[ Woman moans ]

02:35.890 --> 02:37.489
...you are not wrong,

02:37.491 --> 02:42.160
who deem that my days
have been a dream.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.828
[ Gasps ]

02:43.830 --> 02:47.966
Yet if hope has flown away,

02:47.968 --> 02:52.370
in a night or in a day,

02:52.372 --> 02:55.507
in a vision or in none...

02:55.509 --> 02:56.909
[ Animal growls ]

02:56.911 --> 02:59.912
...is it therefore
the less gone?

02:59.914 --> 03:02.046
[ Woman moans ]

03:02.048 --> 03:07.319
All that we see or seem...

03:07.321 --> 03:11.523
is but a dream within a dream.

03:11.525 --> 03:13.726
[ Animal lows ]

03:13.728 --> 03:17.229
♪♪

03:22.002 --> 03:25.004
♪♪

03:29.543 --> 03:33.479
♪♪

03:39.219 --> 03:44.023
♪♪

03:46.893 --> 03:50.229
♪♪

03:57.904 --> 04:01.573
♪♪

04:09.650 --> 04:10.783
Hey, you all right?

04:10.785 --> 04:13.117
Oh. Come on in here,
let me buy you a drink.

04:13.119 --> 04:15.053
[ Laughs ]
So nice to finally meet you.

04:15.055 --> 04:18.590
Look, I can explain some things
to you should know about.

04:18.592 --> 04:22.060
I know things.

04:22.062 --> 04:23.162
[ Grunts ]

04:25.866 --> 04:27.866
♪♪

04:30.270 --> 04:32.937
[ Radio chatter ]

04:32.939 --> 04:34.939
Jennings:
Ma'am, are you okay?

04:34.941 --> 04:37.075
It's not really safe for you
to be by yourself

04:37.077 --> 04:38.677
in this neighborhood,
ma'am.

04:38.679 --> 04:41.213
I'm happy to help you.
Maybe you need a ride home?

04:41.215 --> 04:44.082
[ Radio chatter continues ]

04:44.084 --> 04:45.617
No, thank you, sir.

04:45.619 --> 04:48.687
This is my home.

04:48.689 --> 04:50.889
You and the roaches.

04:50.891 --> 04:53.993
♪♪

04:58.165 --> 05:01.166
[ Siren wails distantly ]

05:01.168 --> 05:04.302
[ Jay snoring ]

05:04.304 --> 05:08.841
♪♪

05:13.848 --> 05:15.980
[ Snorts ]

05:15.982 --> 05:19.451
♪♪

05:24.525 --> 05:27.926
[ Gun clicking ]

05:27.928 --> 05:31.597
♪♪

05:36.403 --> 05:38.671
LAPD, get up!
Get your ass up!

05:38.673 --> 05:40.939
Jay: Oh, shit, what--

05:40.941 --> 05:42.741
Don't worry, cupcake,
you're not under arrest.

05:42.743 --> 05:46.078
-Right there, right there!
-[ Grunting ]

05:46.080 --> 05:47.813
Oh!

05:49.816 --> 05:52.350
What seems to be the problem,
officers?

05:52.352 --> 05:55.954
Tough guy. Don't get so sharp
you chop off your own fingers.

05:55.956 --> 05:58.757
Hey, champ, you see this?
What a psycho.

05:58.759 --> 06:02.160
You jerk off to these, huh?
These your pin-up girls?

06:02.162 --> 06:03.696
Okay. Let's go.

06:03.698 --> 06:06.431
Bring the pervert.

06:06.433 --> 06:09.568
Okay. Okay, okay.
All right. [ Grunts ] Okay.

06:09.570 --> 06:10.469
Man: Come on.

06:12.639 --> 06:15.607
♪♪

06:19.246 --> 06:22.348
Corinna:<i>You're not black,</i>
<i> you boring girl.</i>

06:24.785 --> 06:27.453
♪♪

06:31.191 --> 06:33.325
[ Laughs ] Ernest, stop.

06:33.327 --> 06:35.193
[ Dial tone ]

06:35.195 --> 06:36.395
That damn phone!

06:36.397 --> 06:38.863
-Xander, you need some bacon?
-Let me tell you --

06:38.865 --> 06:40.198
without Willie Mays and Koufax
making peace,

06:40.200 --> 06:42.867
they'd still be fighting
at Candlestick.

06:42.869 --> 06:46.004
Marichal is a son of a gun.
They need to arrest that fool.
Boys,
you need some more bacon?

06:46.006 --> 06:48.607
-No, ma'am, coffee for me.
-Yes, please, Big Momma.

06:48.609 --> 06:50.142
Fauna, you find
your grandma yesterday?

06:50.144 --> 06:53.345
The white one?
Yeah, I did.

06:53.347 --> 06:55.213
And?

06:55.215 --> 06:57.215
[ Chuckles ]

06:57.217 --> 07:00.152
You ever seen a weird,
ugly white man hanging around?

07:00.154 --> 07:01.486
Drives a Buick?

07:01.488 --> 07:03.688
[ Chuckles ]
All white men is ugly.

07:03.690 --> 07:04.823
Got that right.

07:04.825 --> 07:06.759
Mmm,
not that Mick Jagger.

07:06.761 --> 07:08.693
He got some brother
in him.

07:08.695 --> 07:11.830
His lip is all big
at the bottom.

07:15.636 --> 07:18.737
[ Snoring ]

07:22.443 --> 07:24.743
[ Door buzzes ]

07:39.326 --> 07:42.928
[ Creaking loudly ]

07:46.667 --> 07:48.266
[ Handcuffs clank ]

07:48.268 --> 07:50.035
Agh!

07:53.940 --> 07:57.876
You know, they say only
the guilty ones fall asleep.

07:57.878 --> 08:00.412
It's the innocent ones
who are too nervous.

08:00.414 --> 08:02.214
You got me, I did it.

08:05.820 --> 08:08.153
What did I do?

08:08.155 --> 08:09.888
I know
what I'm looking at.

08:09.890 --> 08:11.556
I just twigged it.

08:11.558 --> 08:12.557
Oh, yeah?

08:12.559 --> 08:15.093
Failure.

08:15.095 --> 08:18.363
You're just another hack out
there chasing a hustle.

08:18.365 --> 08:21.900
One worn out decent suit,
the rest cheap crap.

08:21.902 --> 08:24.769
Hiding behind a garbage
can with a camera.

08:24.771 --> 08:26.638
I'm a journalist.

08:26.640 --> 08:28.173
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah, yeah.

08:28.175 --> 08:30.775
Yeah, you're a regular
Ed Murrow,

08:30.777 --> 08:32.945
not some loser shit-bird.

08:34.781 --> 08:36.648
I know
what I'm looking at.

08:36.650 --> 08:38.783
I've seen guys like you
get made.

08:38.785 --> 08:41.319
Is that right?

08:41.321 --> 08:43.856
You're just so scared.

08:43.858 --> 08:47.526
And all that hate you got
in you, it's just...fear.

08:47.528 --> 08:51.530
And the more fear there is, the
more hate until you're just a...

08:51.532 --> 08:53.866
sack of hate...

08:53.868 --> 08:56.801
hiding behind a badge...

08:56.803 --> 08:59.337
hurting people.

08:59.339 --> 09:02.741
What do you know
about hate, cupcake?

09:02.743 --> 09:05.077
Oh, I know everything
there is to know about hate.

09:05.079 --> 09:08.012
Oh, yeah, right.
Right, I remember now.

09:08.014 --> 09:11.015
You was a soldier.
Korea.

09:11.017 --> 09:15.019
You see, the thing about
soldiers in my experience,

09:15.021 --> 09:16.488
is they like
to play tough.

09:16.490 --> 09:19.892
But without orders,
they just fall apart.

09:19.894 --> 09:21.894
Maybe we'll find out
someday.

09:21.896 --> 09:23.295
Maybe we'll find out
today.

09:23.297 --> 09:24.696
What's on your mind,
pal?

09:24.698 --> 09:26.765
You keep turning up
in the wrong places, cupcake.

09:26.767 --> 09:28.233
Whatever
you're sniffing on

09:28.235 --> 09:29.768
got you running
in the wrong direction.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.970
And I feel like
I've already warned you.

09:31.972 --> 09:35.173
So now what do I do?

09:35.175 --> 09:37.309
Oh, and by the way,
you think you're slick?

09:37.311 --> 09:38.911
You ain't slick.

09:38.913 --> 09:41.980
The ex-wife caught you following
her and gave us your plates.

09:43.784 --> 09:45.317
What?

09:45.319 --> 09:48.120
Not the greatest tail man
in the world, are we?

09:48.122 --> 09:50.522
Anyways, I don't necessarily
think it's a good idea

09:50.524 --> 09:52.524
to send a message,
but I'm just the messenger.

09:52.526 --> 09:56.395
Personally, I think we'd be
better off without you.

09:56.397 --> 09:59.798
So the question...

09:59.800 --> 10:03.936
and this is
at my discretion...

10:03.938 --> 10:05.470
is what does it take

10:05.472 --> 10:09.742
to get a message across
to a smart-ass?

10:09.744 --> 10:13.211
Is it a finger?

10:13.213 --> 10:15.147
Is it an eye?

10:15.149 --> 10:17.282
Probably a finger
doesn't mean a great deal

10:17.284 --> 10:22.086
to a genuine war hero
like yourself...

10:22.088 --> 10:24.823
so I think it needs
to be an eye.

10:24.825 --> 10:27.760
♪♪

10:31.565 --> 10:35.668
♪♪

10:38.372 --> 10:40.639
What happened?

10:40.641 --> 10:42.574
Not so chatty anymore?

10:42.576 --> 10:47.846
♪♪

10:47.848 --> 10:51.216
Now, hold still, 'cause this is
gonna really, really hurt.

10:53.253 --> 10:55.454
You gonna kick me?
Kick me?

10:55.456 --> 10:58.590
[ Grunts ]

10:58.592 --> 11:01.660
See, you thought you
knew everything there
was to know about hate.

11:01.662 --> 11:03.395
I want to teach you something
new about hate today.

11:03.397 --> 11:04.797
[ Banging at door ]
Captain: Billis!

11:04.799 --> 11:06.865
Goddamn it!
-[ Grunts ]

11:06.867 --> 11:10.002
-What?!
-Billis, get out here!

11:10.004 --> 11:11.870
Oh, shit!

11:11.872 --> 11:13.271
[ Panting ]

11:13.273 --> 11:16.341
[ Screams ]
[ Door buzzes ]

11:16.343 --> 11:18.410
Captain: I don't care how
protected this monkey is,

11:18.412 --> 11:21.480
he ain't getting away
with this.

11:21.482 --> 11:22.947
What's going on, sir?

11:22.949 --> 11:24.683
That's my investigation
through--

11:24.685 --> 11:25.818
Shut up, Billis.

11:25.820 --> 11:27.352
Shut your face, Ohls.

11:27.354 --> 11:29.221
This ain't your pond.
Enough!

11:29.223 --> 11:31.023
This ain't your pond,
neither, son.

11:31.025 --> 11:32.825
This is
my Goddamn pond.

11:32.827 --> 11:34.626
You got a charge
for that detainee?

11:34.628 --> 11:36.428
No, sir.
Hmm, very well.

11:36.430 --> 11:38.963
Without charges, you can
remand your suspect

11:38.965 --> 11:40.499
over to Detective Ohls.

11:40.501 --> 11:41.433
Sure thing.

11:41.435 --> 11:44.236
Bunch of
Goddamn clowns.

11:44.238 --> 11:45.970
You know what you just did
to your career?

11:45.972 --> 11:47.706
Yeah, I know.
Kaputnik, Sputnik.

11:47.708 --> 11:49.041
I know.
Why?

11:49.043 --> 11:50.709
For that flaky shit-bird?

11:50.711 --> 11:51.976
You wouldn't understand,
Billis.

11:51.978 --> 11:53.378
Come on,
explain it to me.

11:53.380 --> 11:54.646
What, does he keep
your pup-tent warm?

11:54.648 --> 11:57.449
Look,
you weren't there.

11:57.451 --> 12:00.052
You ever heard
of Dog Company?

12:00.054 --> 12:03.022
[ Chuckles ] About
what happened on Hill 1240?

12:04.991 --> 12:06.859
Dog Company sent 200 guys
up that hill,

12:06.861 --> 12:09.394
only 16 ever came off.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.729
I'm hit in both legs,
I'm a dead man.

12:10.731 --> 12:14.867
I don't bleed out
'cause the bullet holes froze.

12:14.869 --> 12:15.868
I might as well have been
on the moon.

12:15.870 --> 12:17.001
Are you following this?

12:17.003 --> 12:19.404
That flaky shit-bird
in there,

12:19.406 --> 12:21.473
I seen him with my own eyes,
Billis.

12:21.475 --> 12:25.477
I seen him run dry and kill
God knows how many of 'em --

12:25.479 --> 12:30.615
oh, seven or eight of 'em
with his entrenching tool.

12:30.617 --> 12:32.084
A shovel.

12:32.086 --> 12:35.254
Just a little
shitty shovel.

12:36.757 --> 12:38.891
So he walks
while I'm alive.

12:42.096 --> 12:44.296
So be it...

12:44.298 --> 12:45.964
Dog Company.

12:47.702 --> 12:50.835
[ Buzzer in distance ]

12:50.837 --> 12:53.305
♪♪

12:53.307 --> 12:55.774
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

12:55.776 --> 13:00.512
♪♪

13:05.452 --> 13:09.955
♪♪

13:20.400 --> 13:21.633
I mean, if you go in there,
man, hold right there.

13:21.635 --> 13:23.435
Fauna: Pulling everyone off
the damn bus,

13:23.437 --> 13:24.903
making 'em sit out in the sun
for two hours for nothin'.

13:24.905 --> 13:27.839
So you saw
your white grandma?

13:27.841 --> 13:29.575
What's she like?
Rich?

13:29.577 --> 13:32.177
Yeah, she was rich and a liar,
hiding things from me.

13:32.179 --> 13:34.246
I think maybe even...

13:34.248 --> 13:37.382
I don't know.
Maybe even Tamar.

13:37.384 --> 13:39.718
-Who's Tamar now?
-She's my real mother.

13:39.720 --> 13:42.187
My birth mother.

13:42.189 --> 13:44.389
I think she was in that house,
hiding.

13:44.391 --> 13:45.791
I'm gonna go back
and find her.

13:45.793 --> 13:48.794
I mean, if I was rich,
I'd get me a color TV.

13:48.796 --> 13:50.462
Shoot, I think
about money plenty.
[ Telephone rings ]

13:50.464 --> 13:53.065
-[ Chuckles ]
-Go on and get that money, girl.

13:53.067 --> 13:55.733
Y'all need
to leave her alone.

13:55.735 --> 13:58.403
She's just looking
for her family.

13:58.405 --> 14:01.607
Big Momma: Pat?
I just want my own room
so I could shut the door.

14:01.609 --> 14:04.476
Pat?!
Fauna, when you get it,
can we come live with you

14:04.478 --> 14:06.078
in your
big white house?

14:06.080 --> 14:08.346
-I ain't about that, Tina.
-Telephone, girl!

14:08.348 --> 14:10.548
How stupid we look?

14:10.550 --> 14:12.918
Just give the girl
some space, man.

14:15.222 --> 14:16.888
You see that?
I saw that.

14:16.890 --> 14:20.426
[ Children playing
in distance ]

14:25.499 --> 14:27.032
Hello?

14:27.034 --> 14:30.836
Hey, uh...girl?

14:30.838 --> 14:34.039
Yeah, this is Nero.

14:34.041 --> 14:35.841
What do you want?

14:35.843 --> 14:37.509
You don't remember me?

14:37.511 --> 14:39.845
The handsome one
from the party.

14:39.847 --> 14:44.182
What do you want?
What do I want?

14:44.184 --> 14:46.384
What do I want?
Come on, what you think I want?

14:46.386 --> 14:48.053
Have you been drinking
already?

14:48.055 --> 14:50.588
Playing hard to get,
you know?

14:50.590 --> 14:52.124
I know all about you.

14:52.126 --> 14:53.925
See, I saw you looking.

14:53.927 --> 14:55.593
Stop calling me,
you snap case.

14:55.595 --> 14:59.064
See, y'all girls, y'all want it
just as bad as dudes.

14:59.066 --> 15:01.133
See,
I got a magic tongue.

15:01.135 --> 15:04.202
And you should
check it out sometime.

15:04.204 --> 15:06.804
[ Dial tone ]

15:06.806 --> 15:09.441
♪♪

15:13.747 --> 15:16.215
♪♪

15:17.685 --> 15:19.751
[ Engine starts ]

15:19.753 --> 15:22.454
♪♪

15:24.492 --> 15:27.092
Hey, you know we're...

15:27.094 --> 15:28.426
we're square.

15:28.428 --> 15:30.696
No, we ain't square.
Ever.

15:30.698 --> 15:32.097
You think you can
stay out of trouble?

15:32.099 --> 15:35.433
Yeah, but see, they...

15:35.435 --> 15:37.503
they wouldn't have dropped the
hammer on me if it was nothing.

15:37.505 --> 15:39.104
They just showed me
that there's something there.

15:39.106 --> 15:40.506
They blew
their whole hand.

15:40.508 --> 15:42.508
Jay, crossing Billis
like that,

15:42.510 --> 15:45.043
that means I've crossed
all kinds of people up

15:45.045 --> 15:47.179
and down the food chain.

15:47.181 --> 15:49.915
He's more connected
than Ma Bell.

15:49.917 --> 15:51.317
Sorry about that.

15:51.319 --> 15:56.054
They are gonna put me on
animal control in Santa Ana...

15:56.056 --> 15:57.723
till I quit
or eat my gun.

15:59.793 --> 16:03.795
I'm out of favors,
you're out of friends.

16:03.797 --> 16:06.198
If they get you again,
you're staying got.

16:09.537 --> 16:11.570
Hop in, Sally.

16:17.010 --> 16:20.746
♪♪

16:25.353 --> 16:28.620
♪♪

16:36.430 --> 16:39.431
♪♪

16:45.705 --> 16:48.474
♪♪

16:55.449 --> 16:57.583
♪♪

17:03.057 --> 17:06.858
♪♪

17:06.860 --> 17:08.994
[ Engine starts ]

17:11.064 --> 17:13.399
♪♪

17:18.538 --> 17:21.040
♪♪

17:27.815 --> 17:30.015
Tamar?

17:30.017 --> 17:32.418
♪♪

17:35.689 --> 17:38.223
[ Lock rattles ]

17:38.225 --> 17:39.725
♪♪

17:42.963 --> 17:44.763
[ Hinge squeals ]

17:44.765 --> 17:47.699
♪♪

17:47.701 --> 17:49.968
[ Gate clangs ]

17:49.970 --> 17:52.237
♪♪

17:59.313 --> 18:01.347
♪♪

18:08.856 --> 18:11.957
♪♪

18:18.265 --> 18:21.500
♪♪

18:27.808 --> 18:29.541
♪♪

18:37.151 --> 18:42.121
♪♪

18:51.098 --> 18:52.430
Peter: And somebody's
gotta be helping Martin

18:52.432 --> 18:53.765
with the civil war thing
in Indonesia.

18:53.767 --> 18:55.300
He can't figure out
the time thing,

18:55.302 --> 18:56.768
so he keeps calling in his sides
when the desk is asleep.

18:56.770 --> 18:58.370
[ Laughter ]
I gotta talk to you guys.

18:58.372 --> 18:59.437
Hello, Jay.
I'm in a meeting here.

18:59.439 --> 19:00.972
Give me 10 minutes,
please.

19:00.974 --> 19:02.240
It's pressing.
Yeah.

19:02.242 --> 19:03.909
Just can you go
have a soda?
Not thirsty.

19:03.911 --> 19:05.577
Go have
a scotch and soda.
Don't drink.

19:05.579 --> 19:07.579
Go have a shot of soda,
for God's sakes!

19:07.581 --> 19:11.049
All right. All right, Tommy, can
you take that one on, please?

19:11.051 --> 19:13.451
Yeah. I know it sucks,
but at least you ain't married.

19:13.453 --> 19:15.787
So take it.

19:15.789 --> 19:18.190
